`    `// Code to execute

}

- Condition is evaluated before entering the loop.
- Loop may not execute at all if condition is false initially.

**Example ŌĆō Print 0 to 9:**

int x = 0;

while (x < 10) {

`    `printf("%d\n", x);

`    `x++;

}

**3. do-while Loop**

**Syntax:**

