`    `scanf("%f", &u.salary);

`    `printf("Emp ID: %d\n", u.ID);        // May not print correctly

`    `printf("Emp Name: %s\n", u.name);    // May not print correctly

`    `printf("Emp Salary: %.2f\n", u.salary);

`    `getch();}
## Pointer to Union
A **pointer to a union** is declared and used similarly to a pointer to structure.
### Syntax:
union team t1;

union team \*sptr;

sptr = &t1;

#include <stdio.h>

